HEADWORD: Pepo
<hw>Pe"po</hw> <pr>(p⟦emac⟧"p⟦osl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a
kind of melon, from Gr. <grk>pe`pwn</grk>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Any fleshy fruit with a firm rind, as a pumpkin, melon, or gourd.
See <er>Gourd</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

